Package utilities

Class LazySearchTree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • utilities.LazySearchTree<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - A generic type to represent any type of data
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable
    public class LazySearchTree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    The LazySearchTree class implements lazy deletion in which nodes are marked as deleted, but not actually removed until specified. When a node is marked as deleted, it is only marked for deletion, but not removed. This is known as soft deletion. Hard deletion occurs when we actually remove the node
